description: The ORDER_PROC_5 table enables you to report on the procedures ordered in the clinical system. This procedure table has the same basic structure as ORDER_PROC, but was created as a fifth table to prevent ORDER_PROC_4 from getting any larger.

columns.name: ORDER_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the order record.

columns.name: FUTURE_RELATIVE_EXPECTED_DT_C_NAME
columns.description:
Holds a category value for the expected completion date. This may be subtly different from the expected date (ORDER_PROC.FUT_EXPECT_COMP_DT) for things like "in 3 months", which could be Start Date+90 days (S+90), Start date+91 days (S+91), or Start date + 92 days (S+92) depending on the current date.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


On Date


Other (specify)


Today


Tomorrow


1 Week


2 Weeks


3 Weeks


4 Weeks


5 Weeks


6 Weeks

4 Months

6 Months


7 Months

9 Months


10 Months


11 Months


12 Months


13 Months


14 Months


15 Months


16 Months


17 Months


18 Months


1 Year


2 Years


3 Years


4 Years


Before Surgery


Before Surgery


Before Next Appt

columns.name: FUTURE_EXPECTED_DATE_COMMENT_C_NAME
columns.description:
Holds a category value for the comment part of expected date. This will include categories based on scheduling comments like "Before Surgery", "After Consult", etc.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: FUTURE_RELATIVE_EXPECTED_DT_C_NAME

columns.name: FUTURE_EXPECTED_DATE_DETAILS
columns.description: This item holds the free-text details entered if the future expected date comment (FUTURE_EXPECTED_DATE_COMMENT_C) is "Other (Specify)".

columns.name: MODIFY_TRACK_C_NAME
columns.description:
Flag used to denote if the order was modified or reordered.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


REORDERED


MODIFIED

columns.name: INCOMPLETE_CHILD_ORDERS
columns.description: Store the number of child orders which have not yet reached completed/canceled status. meaning they are either not yet released or are currently active.

columns.name: ORDER_INST_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: The instant when the order was created in UTC.

columns.name: MINUTES_BTWN_SCHED_AND_COLL
columns.description: The number of minutes between the scheduled and collected instants for a lab.

columns.name: APPT_WINDOW_START_TIME
columns.description: This is the start of the appointment window for the preferred appointment window.

columns.name: OVERREAD_SRC_ORD_ID
columns.description: Stores the order record ID that is marked for imaging overread.

columns.name: APPT_WINDOW_END_TIME
columns.description: This is the end of the appointment window for the preferred appointment window.

columns.name: PROC_ESTIMATE_ID
columns.description: A link to a patient estimate record that contains patient cost estimate information for procedure orders.

columns.name: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN
columns.description:
A flag used for pended orders that indicates that the order should generate a patient estimate record when it is fully signed.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


No


Yes

columns.name: FINANCIAL_CLEARANCE_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description:
Records the financial clearance status of an order


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Cleared


Pending

columns.name: FINANCIAL_CLEARANCE_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: Records the UTC instant an order was financially cleared

columns.name: FNDAVTR_DOC_INFO_ID
columns.description: Stores the Document ID of the image for the findings avatar

columns.name: IMG_PUBLIC_RSLT_DTTM
columns.description: The instant in local time at which the imaging result was made public, as defined by the order's study status (e.g. physician finalized the exam) as configured by the imaging analyst team (I RDF 195).

columns.name: ORDER_RECEIVED_DTTM
columns.description: The date and time the order was received.

columns.name: ACTV_EXCLUDE_FROM_CDS_REASON_C_NAME
columns.description:
The Exclude From Decision Support reason for the order. It will be either 1 - Unsuccessful Attempt represents an order that was not successfully completed. or 2 - Documented on Wrong Patient represents the order's result information was documented on the incorrect patient.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


Unsuccessful Attempt


Documented on Wrong Patient

columns.name: ACTV_EXCLUDE_FROM_CDS_UTC_DTTM
columns.description: The instance in UTC when the "Exclude From Decision Support" was updated on the order record.

columns.name: ACTV_EXCLUDE_FROM_CDS_DTTM
columns.description: The instance when the "Exclude From Decision Support" was updated on the order record.

columns.name: LEAVE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description:
The type of medical leave being ordered.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Outpatient Sick Leave


Hospitalization Leave


Maternity Leave


Light Duty Only


Excuses Only

columns.name: LEAVE_START_DATE
columns.description: Start date of the medical leave.

columns.name: LEAVE_END_DATE
columns.description: End date of the medical leave.

columns.name: LEAVE_DURATION
columns.description: Duration of the medical leave in days.

columns.name: LEAVE_LIGHTDUTY_YN
columns.description:
Whether the medical leave also has a light duty period.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN

columns.name: LEAVE_LIGHTDUTY_START_DATE
columns.description: Start date of the light duty period.

columns.name: LEAVE_LIGHTDUTY_END_DATE
columns.description: End date of the light duty period.

columns.name: LEAVE_LIGHTDUTY_DURATION
columns.description: Duration of the light duty period in days.

columns.name: LEAVE_EXCUSED_ACTIVITIES_YN
columns.description:
Whether the patient should be excused from doing specific activities during the leave.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN

columns.name: LEAVE_EXCUSED_START_DATE
columns.description: Start date of the excused activities period.

columns.name: LEAVE_EXCUSED_END_DATE
columns.description: End date of the excuse period.

columns.name: LEAVE_EXCUSED_DURATION
columns.description: Duration of the excuse period in days.

columns.name: LEAVE_EXCUSED_COMMENTS
columns.description: Comments about the excused activities for the excuse period.

columns.name: DELIVERY_REQUEST_ORDER_ID
columns.description: The order ID of the blood component order this order record is requesting a delivery from.

columns.name: DELIVERY_REQUEST_AMOUNT
columns.description: The number of units being requested from the blood component order record.

columns.name: ORIGINATING_ORD_ID
columns.description: This column contains the originating order ID. It is related conceptually to ORDER_PROC_2.ORIGINAL_ORDER_ID, but rather than pointing back to the previous order ID at the same level in the order tree hierarchy, this column will point back to the initial order created by the ordering end user. Use this column to find out information about the initial order, or to determine if an order went through a change procedure workflow which generated new order records.

columns.name: PROC_CHANGED_YN
columns.description:
This column determines whether the orderable procedure was changed as part of a change procedure workflow that generated new order records. The column will be set to 1 - Yes if a new procedure was selected during the change procedure workflow step. If the procedure was kept and other details were changed, this column will be populated with 0 - No. If the order did not go through a change procedure workflow which generated new order records, this column will be null.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN

columns.name: ACTIVE_PROC_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description:
This item holds the category type of the active procedure order. Only active procedure type orders will be contained in this item. Medications are excluded. The categories separate order type in parent/child/normal and IP/OP order type.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


Active OP Parent Order


Active OP Child Order


Active OP Normal Order


Active IP Parent Order


Active IP Child Order

columns.name: HAS_LAB_SPEC_YN
columns.description:
Indicates whether the order or any of the linked performable orders have a lab specimen. 'Y' indicates that the order or one of the linked performable orders has a lab specimen. 'N' indicates that the order does not have a linked lab specimen and no linked performable order has a lab specimen.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN

columns.name: HAS_RSLT_CNCT_YN
columns.description:
Indicates whether the order has a resulted contact.  'Y' indicates that the order has at least one contact of type 2-Resulted.  'N' indicates that the order does not have any contacts of type 2-Resulted.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN

columns.name: HAS_CORR_YN
columns.description:
Indicates whether the order has a correction. 'Y' indicates that the order has at least one contact with procedure result status equal to 4-Edited or 5-Edited Result - FINAL.  'N' indicates that the order does not have any contacts with procedure result status equal to 4-Edited or 5-Edited Result - FINAL.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: SHOULD_GENERATE_PAT_EST_YN
